# cubesolver
3x3 Cube Solver - Create sequence to solve the cube with a corners first method using Java, display a 2-D GUI.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Author:

Nathen St. Germain
https://github.com/NateSaint
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Using a corners first method, allow user to input their current 3x3 cube scramble and give them a sequence to solve it. Use a 2-D graphical user interface to display each side of the cube as moves are happening. Define the relative position of the cube so the user can follow easy.

Programmed in Java.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compiling:

Compile with makefile by typing "make" while in the cubesolver directory on the command line.  If you cannot run make, compile each .java file individually as seen in makefile.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Usage:

1. Run the file "CubeSolver.java" once everything has been compiled.  Use desired method of running Java programs, I use the command line with the command "java CubeSolver"

2. Click each square to change through the colours available to set current cube scramble

3. Use labelled buttons to select what action to perform
  Reset - reset the cube
  Solve - provide sequence to solve cube
  Quit - exit program
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Features to implement to project:
-Provide sequence to solve
-display in 2-D
-display in 3-D
-create a random sequence generator to experiment with how long it takes to get a sequence of specified length randomly
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
